06/03/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) â The foreign ministers of Austria, Slovenia and Bulgaria -- Michael Spindelegger, Samuel Zbogar and Nikolay Mladenov respectively-- will visit Sarajevo on Monday (March 7th) to meet with members of the BiH tripartite presidency and representatives of the international community. Ahead of the visit, the three diplomats said that BiH needs to form governing bodies at all levels as soon as possible. In a joint article published in Nezavisne Novine on Saturday, they urged Bosnian leaders to focus their efforts on meeting goals related to EU rapprochement, stressing that BiH belongs in the EU. (Radio Free Europe, Nezavisne Novine - 05/03/11) 
